	<h1>Cultural Networks</h1>
	
	<p>
		In the area of digital culture networks, we are interested in understanding the connections and processes between the virtual online networks with our physical world experiences. We are interested in understanding how online artifacts, activities and social relationships are affected by (and in turn affect) events, actions and physical social networks. Our research interests reflect the strengths of faculty from social network analysis, perception, storytelling, media composition and interactive systems design.<br/><br/>
			
